/// 2. Only when the archive has `NoAttestations` *and* `archive_path` is a
///    recognizable multi-file archive is it extracted to a temporary directory
///    and every regular inner file required to have its own valid GitHub
///    artifact attestation under `(owner, repo)`. Directories and symlinks are
///    ignored; a nested archive is treated as an opaque regular file that must
///    itself be attested (it is not recursively unpacked). If **any** regular
///    inner file is unattested, or fails verification, the whole archive is
///    rejected. Extraction failures and single-file/compressed payloads are not
