+///    attestations exist for the archive but fail to verify, that failure is
+///    surfaced and the inner-file fallback never runs.
+/// 2. Only when the archive has `NoAttestations` *and* `archive_path` is a
+///    recognizable multi-file archive is it extracted to a temp directory and
+///    every regular inner file required to have its own valid GitHub artifact
+///    attestation under `(owner, repo)`. Directories and symlinks are ignored;
+///    a nested archive is treated as an opaque regular file that must itself be
+///    attested (it is not recursively unpacked). If **any** regular inner file
+///    is unattested, or fails verification, the whole archive is rejected.
+/// 3. Extraction failures and single-file/compressed payloads (`.gz`, `.xz`,
+///    raw binaries) are not treated as archives here, so the original
+///    `NoAttestations` result is returned and callers' existing SLSA/unavailable
+///    fallbacks run unchanged.
